profile_positions.description:
In addition to the projects described below my current responsibilities also include:
•	Participation in projects related to conclusion of special investment contracts (SPIC), incl. analysis of potential state support measures (tax and non-tax measures, including tax concessions, subsidies, infrastructure support, access to public purchases, etc.), structuring of project, choosing optimal contract model, packaging rights and obligations of the investor within SPIC and giving  recommendations on their shaping to minimize tax and legal risks along with investor’s obligations and liabilities, participation in negotiations with state authorities;
•	Comparative analysis of federal/regional tax concessions (SPIC, regional investment projects, special economic zones, other preferential tax regimes) available to the investors taking into account specifics of the investment projects. Assistance in agreeing and obtaining federal/regional tax concessions;
•	Participation in projects related to introduction of amendments into tax legislation, incl. elaboration of legal and economic justifications, elaboration of draft law provisions, participation in negotiations with business associations and state authorities.

Corporate Tax, Consumer Industrial Products / Telecommunication & Media

Extensive experience in managing provision of tax consulting services to the clients, including:
•	Tax structuring of transactions, participation in restructuring of Russian and foreign holding companies, including development of effective corporate structure, including cross-border transactions;
•	Advisory services on restructuring of holding companies including reorganization of the company’s holding structure, structure of its sales, financial, investment and other operations for the purposes of tax optimization and in order to make companies more transparent and attractive for potential investors (for example, in the course of preparation for an IPO);
•	Structuring, analysis and preparation of a file supporting intragroup services and the funding structure;
•	Providing advice on transfer pricing regulations and preparation of transfer pricing documentation;
•	Providing advice on application of Russian controlled foreign companies rules and structuring of Russian businesses in foreign jurisdictions to comply with these rules; 
•	Tax review/audit of Russian and foreign companies according to IAS and RAS.

Corporate Tax, Metals & Mining/Oil& Gas

Extensive experience in managing provision of tax consulting services to the clients, including:
•	Tax structuring of transactions, participation in restructuring of Russian and foreign holding companies, including development of effective corporate structure, including cross-border transactions;
•	Advisory services on restructuring of holding companies including reorganization of the company’s holding structure, structure of its sales, financial, investment and other operations for the purposes of tax optimization and in order to make companies more transparent and attractive for potential investors (for example, in the course of preparation for an IPO);
•	Providing advice on transfer pricing regulations and preparation of transfer pricing documentation;
•	Providing advice on application of Russian controlled foreign companies rules and structuring of Russian businesses in foreign jurisdictions to comply with these rules; 
•	Tax advisory services for Russian and foreign companies, including development of tax accounting policy and methodology of tax accounting (i.a. for the purposes of implementation of enterprise information systems (SAP ERP, etc.));
•	Structuring, analysis and preparation of a file supporting intragroup services and the funding structure;
•	Tax review/audit of Russian and foreign companies according to IAS and RAS.

Managing consulting work (including delivering solutions to clients, managing client relationships, establishing and supporting of efficient relationships with clients, control over financial results of engagements/projects, supervising of work and developing of junior team members) in the following areas:
•	Tax structuring of transactions, development of effective corporate structure of Russian and foreign holding companies;
•	Tax advisory services for Russian and foreign companies, including development of tax accounting policy and methodology of tax accounting (i.a. for the purpose of implementation of enterprise information systems (SAP ERP, etc.));
•	Participation in supporting oil & gas companies in obtaining tax and customs preferences, including companies operating in the Russian continental shelf;
•	Providing advice on transfer pricing regulations and preparation of transfer pricing documentation;
•	Participation in tax part of Due Diligence;
•	Drafting of tax sections of offering memorandum during public offering (IPO, SPO);
•	Tax review/audit of Russian and foreign companies according to IAS and RAS.

Participation in project as a senior team member (leading a group of consultants and senior consultants by providing effective delegation, supervision and on job coaching) in the following areas:
•	Participation in tax projects, delivering solutions to clients, including tax planning, consulting, analysis of tax consequence and tax risks;
•	Preparation of commercial proposals for tax consulting services, preparation of marketing materials;
•	Participation in tax audit;
•	Participation in Due Diligence.
